2ï¸âƒ£ Log Analytics
ğŸ”¹ Definition (where all monitoring data is stored, queried, and analyzed.â€)

Log Analytics is a feature inside Azure Monitor.
Itâ€™s a workspace where all logs (activity logs, metrics, diagnostics, etc.) are collected and stored for querying and analysis using Kusto Query Language (KQL).

ğŸ”¹ Purpose
It helps you query logs, detect issues, and analyze root causes.

ğŸ”¹ ExampleğŸ‘‡
Azure Monitor detects high CPU on your VM.
You open Log Analytics Workspace and run a KQL query:
Perf
| where ObjectName == "Processor"
| summarize AvgCPU = avg(CounterValue) by bin(TimeGenerated, 5m)
This shows CPU usage every 5 mins.
You find that a specific process (w3wp.exe) spikes CPU â€” youâ€™ve found the root cause.
